OL,7,F"And that's tragic really because it
OL,8,Fmeans that this whole bank of
OL,9,Fknowledge that exists around that
OL,10,Findividual wasn't accessed as part of
OL,11,Fthat assessment process and as a
OL,12,Fconsequence of that the assessment was
OL,13,Fnecessarily and inevitably flawed."
OL,15,FHe added: "I think it was negligent on
OL,16,Fthe part of the council and I
OL,17,Fdefinitely believe it to be illegal."
