OL,4,Ccuts after 'unsafe assessments', say
OL,5,Cfamilies
OL,7,FThat is a prospect facing Phillip
OL,8,FBrown, who is autistic and has Down
OL,9,FSyndrome. He loves the home he lives
OL,10,Fin, he tells us, as he proudly shows
OL,11,Fus around his room adorned with his
OL,12,Fcolourful artwork and family
OL,13,Fphotographs.
OL,15,FHe is settled and enjoys his routine -
OL,16,Fbut that is now under threat with the
OL,17,Fcouncil planning to cut his hours of
OL,18,Fsupport by three quarters. This means
OL,19,Fhis one to one hours are being cut
OL,20,Fdown from 40 a week to 11.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/32
