OL,7,FThe decision was made after they
OL,8,Freassessed his needs without his
OL,9,Fmother there to advocate for him
OL,10,Fbecause they failed to carry out a
OL,11,Fmental capacity assessment to
OL,12,Fdetermine whether he had the capacity
OL,13,Fto understand what was happening.
OL,15,F"If Phillip had been asked, 'would you
OL,16,Flike your mum here?' Phillip would
OL,17,Fhave said yes, because Phillip knows
OL,18,FI'm always here with him," she said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/32
