OL,7,F"He presents well, but his
OL,8,Funderstanding is not particularly
OL,9,Fgood, which is why we are always
OL,10,Fthere. We understand him and we could
OL,11,Fhave at least put it in a way that
OL,12,FPhillip might understand."
OL,14,FAsked how she felt when she discovered
OL,15,Fshe'd been excluded from advocating
OL,16,Ffor her son, she replied: "The way
OL,17,Fthat the assessment has been carried
OL,18,Fout, I would say is illegal."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/32
