OL,7,FMatthew, who is learning disabled and
OL,8,Fautistic, has lived in the house,
OL,9,Fwhich he shares with three other
OL,10,Flearning disabled men, for almost 30
OL,11,Fyears.
OL,13,FHe arrived at the house, aged 19, at a
OL,14,Ftime when he was so distressed he had
OL,15,Fstopped eating and drinking completely.
OL,17,F"He was really unhappy and quite
OL,18,Fdisturbed," Andrew explained. "He had
OL,19,Fa lot of eating disorders, he wouldn't
OL,20,Feat for long periods of time and he
OL,21,Fwas fed through a peg in his stomach.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/32
