OL,7,FHowever, Surrey denies mental capacity
OL,8,Fassessments need to be carried out on
OL,9,FMatthew, Phillip and the majority of
OL,10,Fthe other adults affected.
OL,12,FWhat is the Mental Capacity Act and
OL,13,Fhow could the law change?
OL,15,FThe Mental Capacity Act was introduced
OL,16,Fin 2005 in a bid to minimise the
OL,17,Fnumber of vulnerable adults being
OL,18,Fdetained unreasonably and
OL,19,Findefinitely, and to give them more
OL,20,Fautonomy over their own care.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/32
