OL,3,CLearning disabled adults face care
OL,4,Ccuts after 'unsafe assessments', say
OL,5,Cfamilies
OL,7,FIt states that as a starting point,
OL,8,Feveryone should be presumed to have
OL,9,Fthe capacity to make decisions about
OL,10,Ftheir own safety and wellbeing, and
OL,11,Fthat an assessment should be carried
OL,12,Fout if their capacity is in doubt.
OL,14,FHowever, research has found that such
OL,15,Fassessments are either not carried out
OL,16,Fenough or are not carried out
OL,17,Feffectively - in particular on
OL,18,Fautistic people, adults with learning
OL,19,Fdisabilities or those with severe
OL,20,Fmental health conditions, such as
OL,21,Fbipolar and schizophrenia.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G22/32
